I get this random message from people on Linkedin ALL the time (at least 10 times a day).  Let me answer everyone at once...
"I am great, thank you for asking"
Personally, I ignore ALL of the messages that say "how are you doing?"  In today's fast paced world, you need to either bring an ASK or a GIVE to any conversation.
NOTE:  ****PEOPLE READ THIS***  The point isn't that I don't want people to ask how I'm doing, the point is they NEVER get to the point they want to make.  GET TO THE POINT!!!!
ASK:  "Can you introduce me to XYZ?"
GIVE:  "I noticed you are in VR, we make ZYX product that might be great for you, check it out  [Insert link to webpage]"

Common courtesy dictates that you be concise and polite, but wasting time asking people how they are is just not necessary on this platform.  Assume everyone is great (that is the answer you are going to get anyway)
Please, when messaging people on LinkedIn, get to the point, ask or give but don't waste time.

Also, please do NOT write me a book about what you do.  If you can't get to the point in 2 lines or less, you are writing too much.  Send me a link so I can research on my own time.  Messages with a book get ignored.
